<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="438" pageId="25" pageNumber="437" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[816,1429,1925,2019]" box="[816,919,1925,1951]" pageId="25" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis box="[816,919,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="437">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[816,1429,1925,2019]" lastBlockId="26.[159,772,220,1514]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="438" pageId="25" pageNumber="437">
The records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[1050,1193,1959,1985]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="437" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1050,1193,1959,1985]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="437">Miniopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species for 
<collectingRegion country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="25" pageNumber="437">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
are not consistent among previous studies. 
<bibRefCitation author="VAN STRIEN, N. J." firstAuthor="van Strien" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="438" pageId="25" pageNumber="437" refId="ref28803" refString="VAN STRIEN, N. J. 1996. The checklist mammal fauna of the Gunung Leuser National Park. Pp. 133 - 203, in Leuser: a Sumatran sanctuary (C. P. VAN SCHAIK and J. SUPRIATNA, eds.). Yayasan Bina Sains Hayati Indonesia, Depok, iv + 348 pp." type="book" year="1996">van Strien (1996)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Suyanto" box="[374,617,220,246]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Suyanto" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref28408" refString="SUYANTO, A., M. YONEDA, I. MARYANTO, MAHARADATUNKAMSI, and J. SUGARDJITO. 1998. Checklist of the mammals of Indonesia: scientific name and distribution area table in Indonesia including CITES, IUCN and Indonesian category for conservation. LIPI-JICA, Bogor, vii + 34 pp." type="book" year="1998">
Suyanto 
<emphasis box="[479,538,220,246]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">et al.</emphasis>
(1998
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Suyanto" box="[631,691,220,246]" firstAuthor="Suyanto" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref28464" refString="SUYANTO, A., M. YONEDA, I. MARYANTO, MAHARADATUNKAMSI, and J. SUGARDJITO. 2002. Checklist of the mammals of Indonesia: scientific name and distribution area table in Indonesia including CITES, IUCN and Indonesian category for conservation, 2 nd edition. LIPI-JICA-PHKA, Bogor, vii + 63 pp." type="book" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
) listed three species for the island: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1835" box="[540,719,254,280]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fuliginosus">
<emphasis box="[540,719,254,280]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. fuliginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[159,340,289,315]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schreibersii">
<emphasis box="[159,340,289,315]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. schreibersii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the studies, but see 
<bibRefCitation author="Tian" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Tian" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" pagination="303 - 311" refId="ref28636" refString="TIAN, L., B. LIANGI, K. MAEDA, W. METZNER, and S. ZHANG. 2004. Molecular studies on the classification of Miniopterus schreibersii (Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae) inferred from mitochondrial cytochrome b sequences. Folia Zoologica, 53: 303 - 311." type="journal article" year="2004">
Tian 
<emphasis box="[700,764,289,315]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">et al.</emphasis>
, 2004
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sanborn" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[243,396,323,349]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnater">
<emphasis box="[243,396,323,349]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. magnater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[464,596,323,349]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[464,596,323,349]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the records of 
<taxonomicName box="[283,413,357,383]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[283,413,357,383]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(also see 
<bibRefCitation author="Whitten" box="[528,763,357,383]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Whitten" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref28927" refString="WHITTEN, A. J., S. J. DAMNIK, J. ANWAR, and N. HISYAM. 2000. Chapter Ten: caves. Pp. 313 - 336, in The ecology of Sumatra, 1 st periplus edition. Tuttle Publishing, North Clarendo, xxxix + 478 pp." type="book" year="2000">
Whitten 
<emphasis box="[630,688,357,383]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">et al.</emphasis>
, 2000
</bibRefCitation>
) were not included in subsequent reviews (
<bibRefCitation author="Corbet and Hill" firstAuthor="Corbet" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref25099" refString="CORBET, G. B., and J. E. HILL. 1992. The mammals of the Indomalayan Region: a systematic review. Natural History Museum Publications, Oxford, 488 pp." type="book" year="1992">Corbet and Hill 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons" box="[336,524,426,452]" firstAuthor="Simmons" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref27949" refString="SIMMONS, N. B. 2005. Order Chiroptera. Pp. 312 - 529, in Mammal species of the world: a taxonomic and geographic reference, 3 rd edition (D. E. WILSON and D. M. REEDER, eds.). The Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, xxxv + 2142 pp." type="book" year="2005">Simmons, 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Boitani" box="[536,766,426,452]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Boitani" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref24868" refString="BOITANI, L., I. CATULLO, M. MARZETTI, M. MASI, M. RULLI, and S. SAVINI. 2006. The Southeast Asian mammal databank. A tool for conservation and monitoring of mammal diversity in Southeast Asia. Instituto di Ecologia Applicata, Rome. Available at www. ieaitaly. org / samd /." type="book" year="2006">
Boitani 
<emphasis box="[630,689,426,452]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">et al.</emphasis>
, 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[159,309,460,486]" firstAuthor="IUCN" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref26437" refString="IUCN 2013. IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2013.1. &lt;www. iucnredlist. org&gt;. Last accessed on 4 th July 2013." type="book" year="2013">IUCN, 2013</bibRefCitation>
). An additional species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[595,737,460,486]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[595,737,460,486]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is listed for 
<collectingRegion box="[270,368,494,520]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
by a few recent studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Boitani" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Boitani" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref24868" refString="BOITANI, L., I. CATULLO, M. MARZETTI, M. MASI, M. RULLI, and S. SAVINI. 2006. The Southeast Asian mammal databank. A tool for conservation and monitoring of mammal diversity in Southeast Asia. Instituto di Ecologia Applicata, Rome. Available at www. ieaitaly. org / samd /." type="book" year="2006">
Boitani 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">et al.</emphasis>
, 2006
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[286,440,528,554]" firstAuthor="IUCN" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref26437" refString="IUCN 2013. IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2013.1. &lt;www. iucnredlist. org&gt;. Last accessed on 4 th July 2013." type="book" year="2013">IUCN, 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Due to similarities in appearance, the classification of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[525,668,563,589]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[525,668,563,589]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains uncertain, which makes species identification in the field difficult (
<bibRefCitation author="Francis" box="[332,500,631,657]" firstAuthor="Francis" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" refId="ref25558" refString="FRANCIS, C. M. 2008. A guide to mammals of Southeast Asia. Princeton University Press, Princeton, NJ, 392 pp." type="book" year="2008">Francis, 2008</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, we recognize three morphologically distinct species in our samples, and assign names to three of the four known species (see species accounts below). Further studies of craniodental measurements and genetic relationships are necessary to confirm our identifications.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[159,772,220,1514]" lastBlockId="26.[816,1429,220,587]" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[197,451,871,897]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[197,451,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the smallest of the three recognized species from our study area. Comparing with known 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[307,450,940,966]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[307,450,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in the Sunda shelf, the forearm length, body mass, and tibia length of the bat overlapped largely with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[555,702,1008,1034]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[555,702,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other localities, but were smaller than all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[159,302,1077,1103]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[159,302,1077,1103]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<tableCitation box="[430,533,1077,1103]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="26.[159,172,1595,1616]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="TABLE 4. Selected external traits and distribution of known Miniopterus species on the Sunda Shelf and this study. FA â€” forearm length (mm), BM â€” body mass (g), TB â€” tibia length (mm). Data in parentheses denote samples of this study" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/1DCD6623FFB8BF219994F9D9FB777019" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" tableUuid="1DCD6623FFB8BF219994F9D9FB777019">Table 4</tableCitation>
). Individuals were characterized by orange-yellow and flesh-colored skin of the face and tragus, which was not observed in the other two 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[367,510,1179,1205]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[367,510,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Miniopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in our study. Similar coloration is seen in 
<taxonomicName box="[559,695,1214,1240]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="medius">
<emphasis box="[559,695,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. medius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[296,404,1248,1274]" name="Malaysia" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
but not in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[553,701,1248,1274]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis box="[553,701,1248,1274]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="438">M. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Borneo (J. Senawi, personal communication). However, coloration is seldom used as a diagnostic trait to identify cave-roosting insectivorous bats in Southeast Asia because variations in color among individuals and geographic populations are commonly found in many species. Although this color pattern is stable in our samples, in the present study, we assign this species as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tomes" authorityYear="1858" box="[1127,1272,220,246]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="438" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
